On April 9, 2009, President Barack Obama issued a Presidential Memorandum regarding the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) Office. The memorandum states that the President has determined and certified that it is important to the national security interests of the United States to waive the provisions of Section 1003 of the Anti-Terrorism Act of 1987, Public Law 100-204. This waiver will be effective for a period of 6 months. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to transmit this determination to Congress and publish it in the Federal Register.